<br>
Some of us cannot move around as freely because of our race (Troll, Ogre, Dark Elf).  I accept that as part of the game and refuse to bemoan my fate.  It was by free will that I decided to play a Troll.<br>
<br>
My purpose of this topic is to compile helpful hints and advice by experienced (or new) players of dark races (I hate using that designation!  We're just misunderstood!).  What do you think?  <br>
<br>
One of my favorite places to hunt is Butcherblock but as a Troll I'm unable to travel their easily (or safely).  No worries, I like the challenge but why not share what I learn with everyone else in the guild (and out).<br>
<br>
I'll be travelling to Butcherblock with Razgum tonigh and if all goes well, I'll get there via the boat from Oasis to Kunark, then from Kunark to Butcherblock (along with the swim! hehehehe). <br>
<br>
I'll write up my observations and add them to this topic after my little trip.<br>
<br>
Razgum<br>
Troll Shaman of the 8th season/Travel Agent of the 1st <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub12.ezboard.com/udespaire.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Despaire</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>   <font color=#006400>(8/16/00 4:27:48 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Dark Race travel guide</span><hr size=1> While I can sympathize with your desire to hunt a familiar territory, I cannot for the life of me understand why you would want to leave the wonderful swamp and South Ro (one of the most underhunted zones in Norrath) and for that matter Upper Guk.  There is also the lizards, orcs and basalisks (these in the mid-upper teens) of Rathe Mtns to hunt...  Lavastorm is great for early teens (even pre-teens) - just be sure and get your Grobb Oven Mitts!<br>
<br>
Of course, you do realize that I could teleport your big green butt to GFay, don't you? <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   <br>
<br>
Despaire D'vie <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub12.ezboard.com/urazgum.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Razgum</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>   <font color=#006400>(8/16/00 4:46:38 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Dark Race travel guide</span><hr size=1> It's the travel bug in me!  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   I love to travel around even if it does hurt my leveling.  I totally agree that a Troll (or Ogre) doesn't need to go to Butcherblock to hunt and can be very happy in his or her home territory as you pointed out <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Big green butt!  I'm insulted!  For your information I have a very nice dancing figure!  Hehehehehe :P  <br>
<br>
Stay safe!<br>
<br>
Razgum<br>
Troll Shaman of the 8th season<br>
<br>
   <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub12.ezboard.com/utenylar.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Tenylar</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_greenspot.gif BORDER=0 WIDTH=10 HEIGHT=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>   <font color=#006400>(8/17/00 10:50:26 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://home.wtal.de/madman/teny.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Dark Race travel guide</span><hr size=1> There would also be the direct way through Freeport...yes, I said Freeport <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :p --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":p"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
