<br>
I know my way around, and know that if I need to go anywhere, I can just take some short cuts.<br>
<br>
If I need to go to the karana side of the world I just go through rathe mountains. <br>
<br>
I have not had any travel or hunting problems yet.<br>
<br>
I am saving my frogglok meet so that I can make Ogre stout. har har me want gud Alcohol tolerence.<br>
<br>
You know many people don't know the perpose of alcohol in the game. Poeple think its to just have fun and act silly, but thats not it at all.<br>
<br>
Its so that when you get to a point that you can drink a good amount that you don't get drunk, you can use the Str stats that it gives you. If you never noticed it try it out. you get Str stats gud for the more you drink. I will carrie about 40 drinks just for fighting when I was Tindar.<br>
<br>
Respectfully,<br>
Tindar Hearted <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub12.ezboard.com/urazgum.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Razgum</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>   <font color=#006400>(8/31/00 5:16:19 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: I got to agree with Despaire</span><hr size=1> Hi all!  Razgum here.<br>
<br>
To some extent I've &quot;mastered&quot; the &quot;getting from Butcherblock to Freeport and visa versa&quot; trip with little danger.  I, for one, have the travel bug.  If I could travel from one end of Norrath to the other I would do so.  As all you know traveling through Kunark was a study in frustration for me <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   My fault entirely for the deep doo-doo I got myself into.  <br>
<br>
Again, before I travel I think:  Listen to Despaire!  Or ask for a TP!  Heheheh  You are the best Despaire! <br>
<br>
For those new Trolls and Ogres thinking on traveling in a non-teleporting fashion here is some advice:<br>
<br>
Level:  I adventured out of Innothule at 6th level.  Way to low for a Troll to do so, IMHO.  It's really up to you but remember, you'll have to make the run through Southern Ro, Oasis, and Northern Ro to get to East Freeport.<br>
<br>
Swim, Swim, Swim:  Raise your Swim skill up as much (and as fast) as you can.  For trolls, it's relatively easy since we live in a swamp.  Ogres, go to Innothule and swim away! <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Freeport to Butcherblock:   Go to East Freeport and find the tunnel system which will lead you to the ports.  You'll have to swim for the docks.  BEWARE!  I've been killed by the Fisher woman on the docks by getting too close.  I recommend swimming out and then towards the dock she fishes off, making a wide arch around her to the rocks on the other side.  You should be able to sit there and wait for the ship.  You can find a map of the tunnels under Freeport on EQAtlas (<!--EZCODE AUTOLINK START--><a href="http://www.eqatlas.com).">www.eqatlas.com).</a><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK END--><br>
<br>
Once the ship arrives swim out in front of it and when it starts moving you'll be sucked up into the ship.  When you reach the Isle of Tears stay below deck or away from the NPC.  She con'ed indifferent to me but I tend to be paranoid.<br>
<br>
Once in Butcherblock swim for either the land to your left for right on the other side of the walls.  Watch out!  There are Dwarves there that are KOS to Evil Races.  Now that you're in BB, stay away from all Houses and guards.  You should be fine.<br>
<br>
Again, there is always Teleporting!  Hehehehehe<br>
<br>
I'll add Getting from Butcherblock to Freeport tomorrow.  <br>
<br>
I hope this has helped and if you have any questions or want to add your own comment, by all means, do so <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
See you online!<br>
<br>
Razgum<br>
Troll Travelguide of the 8th season<br>
